i remember a foul mouth guy with hatred for blacks, browns, jews, anyone and everyone. He worked 77th for awhile, and then was one of the cowards that left the LAPD when Willie Williams, who was an incompetent political appointment as chief, and black, came on board to replace D. Gates. Gates was a good Chief, backed his man, Wiliams couldn't even carry a weapon, not POST certified. Whata a joke he was.<br><br>
This foul mouth was a guy named barella or something like that, a real bully, and we were all glad we moved on.  Looks like he found a home here, with similar bigots.  I mean this guy was totally stupid. No one wanted to pull a shift with him.<br><br>
I never met spatz or his group, but I wished I had. My lawyer tried to get me to go to him. He got alot of ex nam cops off work, on medical retirements, cause we were just burned out. Too much warfare, jungles or streets. My lawyer said to go there, but I didn't want to go to Orange County. Result was I went to some local whore-doctor and lost my disability case.  Anyway, I had a transfer in for robbery homicide and it came through, so I got off the streets of hatred and crack, and my attitude got better.<br><br>
If you hear this attitude,and I for one sure read it, in the writing of Barella, or Cook, or whatever name he is hiding behind, you have to understand his background. From nam and black P.J. wearing AK-47 shooting commies he comes home, gets unwelcomed and spit on, and then ends up with Afro-Americans, i.e. bloods and crips, shooting AK-47's at him again, but this time he has a vest, and is a cop. It fries his ass, and his brain over time. It did it to mine, I know.<br><br>
Problem is that he don't know how he sounds to others, and how burned out and fried he is, and the rest of you losers feed into him, like lets see how far we can make him go before he explodes.  hey barberella, don't be played for the fool, get help. it works.
